data.content:
Lustre文件系统
Lustre文件系统is a distributed file system designed for high-performance computing environments, supporting large-scale data storage and access across multiple nodes.<SEP>Lustre文件系统is a distributed file system designed for high-performance computing environments, supporting large-scale data storage and access.<SEP>Lustre是一个高性能、可扩展的分布式文件系统，支持POSIX标准，具备高可用性、数据完整性及多种网络协议。

ZFS
ZFS is a file system and logical volume manager designed for high reliability, performance, and data integrity, often used as a backend storage solution for Lustre.<SEP>ZFS是一种用于存储可靠性的文件系统，被Lustre用来确保数据的完整性和可靠性。

RDMA
RDMA (Remote Direct Memory Access) is a network technology that allows for fast and low-latency data transfer between nodes, supported by Lustre for high-performance I/O.<SEP>RDMA(远程直接内存访问)是一种高速网络技术，被Lustre支持以提高数据传输效率。

MGS
MGS is a Management Service that manages the Lustre file system configuration and communication between components.<SEP>MGS(管理服务器)是Lustre文件系统的核心组件之一，负责管理元数据目标(MGT)。

MDS
MDS (Metadata Server) is a component of the Lustre file system that manages metadata operations, such as file creation, deletion, and access control.<SEP>MDS(元数据服务器)是Lustre文件系统的组件之一，负责处理元数据操作。<SEP>Metadata Server (MDS) is a component of the Lustre file system responsible for managing metadata, such as file names and directory structures.

MDT
MDT (Metadata Target) is a component of the Lustre file system responsible for storing metadata about files and directories, including information about their location on OSTs.<SEP>MDT is a metadata target that stores metadata for the Lustre file system. It is configured on dedicated nodes and works with the Metadata Client (MDC) to provide transparent access to multiple MDTs.<SEP>MDT(元数据目标)是Lustre文件系统中存储元数据的组件，主MDT保存根目录，其他MDT可用于子目录。<SEP>Metadata Target (MDT) is a component of the Lustre file system that stores metadata for files and directories.

OSS
OSS (Object Storage Server) is a component of the Lustre file system that manages data storage on OSTs, providing I/O services for client access.<SEP>OSS is an object storage service that provides file IO services and network requests for one or more local OSTs. It is configured on dedicated nodes and serves between two to eight OSTs, each with a maximum capacity of 16TiB.<SEP>OSS(对象存储服务)为OST提供I/O服务，每个OST存储文件数据。<SEP>Object Storage Server (OSS) is a component of the Lustre file system that stores data objects and handles data I/O operations.

OST
OST (Object Storage Target) is a component of the Lustre file system that stores actual file data, allowing for scalable and parallel data access across multiple storage devices.<SEP>OST is an object storage target where user file data is stored in one or more objects, each located in a separate OST within the Lustre file system. Each file's object count is configurable based on workload performance needs.<SEP>OST(对象存储目标)是Lustre文件系统中存储文件数据的组件。<SEP>Object Storage Target (OST) is a component of the Lustre file system that stores data objects on disk.

MDC
MDC is a metadata client that interacts with MDTs to manage metadata operations in the Lustre file system.<SEP>MDC(元数据客户端)是客户端组件，用于访问Lustre文件系统的元数据。

OSC
OSC is an object storage client that interacts with OSTs to manage data operations in the Lustre file system.<SEP>OSC(对象存储客户端)是客户端组件，用于访问Lustre文件系统的数据存储。

LNet
LNet is the networking layer of the Lustre file system, enabling communication between Lustre components over various network technologies.<SEP>LNet is the networking layer of the Lustre file system, enabling communication between clients and servers.<SEP>LNet是Lustre的网络通信基础设施，负责节点之间的通信。

FID
FID(文件标识符)用于唯一标识Lustre文件系统中的文件。<SEP>File Identifier (FID) is a 128-bit unique identifier used by Lustre to replace UNIX inode numbers for identifying files and objects.

LFSCK
LFSCK (Lustre File System Check) is a tool used to verify and repair consistency between MDT and OST components in the Lustre file system.<SEP>LFSCK is a file system consistency check tool used to verify the consistency of file objects between MDTs and OSTs in the Lustre file system.<SEP>LFSCK是Lustre文件系统提供的灾难恢复工具，用于检查和修复文件系统一致性。

llstat
llstat is a command-line utility used to monitor and display statistics related to Lustre file system components such as MDTs, OSTs, and other subsystems.<SEP>llstat是Lustre文件系统中用于监控文件系统统计信息的工具。

llverdev
llverdev is a command-line tool used for device validation in the Lustre file system. It allows users to perform partial or full verification of storage devices.<SEP>llverdev is a utility used to verify the integrity of block devices, ensuring that data can be written and read correctly without corruption.<SEP>llverdev是Lustre文件系统中用于验证块设备完整性的工具。

lshowmount
lshowmount是Lustre文件系统中用于显示Lustre导出信息的工具。

lst
lst is a command used to initiate LNet self-tests, ensuring proper installation and configuration of the Lustre networking layer.<SEP>lst是Lustre文件系统中用于启动LNet自检的命令。

NFS
NFS是一种网络文件系统协议，Lustre可通过NFS导出文件系统。

CIFS
CIFS是一种网络文件系统协议，Lustre可通过CIFS导出文件系统。

Linux
Linux是Lustre文件系统运行的操作系统平台。

GPL 2.0
GPL 2.0是Lustre文件系统的开源许可证，允许自由使用和修改代码。

细粒度元数据锁定
细粒度元数据锁定是Lustre的功能之一，允许多个客户端同时读取和修改相同文件或目录，确保一致性。

配额管理
配额管理是Lustre文件系统的一项功能，用于限制用户和组的存储使用。

文件布局控制
文件布局控制是Lustre的功能，允许在文件、目录或文件系统级别配置跨OST的文件布局。

灾难恢复工具
灾难恢复工具是Lustre提供的功能，包括LFSCK工具，用于检查和修复文件系统一致性。

性能监视
性能监视是Lustre提供的功能，包含多种机制用于检查性能和进行调整。

RAID-0条带化
RAID-0条带化是Lustre的存储策略，用于在OST之间分布文件数据以提高性能。

网络数据完整性保护
网络数据完整性保护是Lustre的功能，通过校验和防止数据在传输期间损坏。

MPI I/O
MPI I/O是Lustre架构中优化并行I/O的专用层。

Management Server (MGS)
Management Server (MGS) is responsible for storing configuration information for all Lustre file systems and providing this information to other Lustre components.

Metadata Server (MDS)
Metadata Server (MDS) manages metadata for the Lustre file system, including file names, directories, and permissions, and provides network request handling for one or more Metadata Targets (MDTs).

Metadata Target (MDT)
Metadata Target (MDT) stores metadata on the MDS's attached storage, such as file names, directories, permissions, and file layout.

Object Storage Server (OSS)
Object Storage Server (OSS) is responsible for storing and managing the actual data objects in the Lustre file system.

Lustre Clients
Lustre Clients are the end-user systems that access the Lustre file system over a network, using either Ethernet or InfiniBand.

FID-in-dirent
FID-in-dirent is a feature in the Lustre file system that allows files across multiple MDTs to be identified and accessed independently.<SEP>FID-in-dirent is a feature in the Lustre file system that stores the File Identifier (FID) within the directory entry, enabling faster lookup and path reconstruction.<SEP>FID-in-dirent is a feature that allows the Lustre file system to identify files across multiple MDTs, providing backward compatibility with version 1.8 of the Idiskfs disk format.

/dev/sda
/dev/sda is a block device representing a physical storage drive used in the Lustre file system configuration.

Timestamp
Timestamp refers to a specific point in time recorded during operations in the Lustre file system, often used for tracking changes or events.

showmount
showmount is a command-line utility used to display information about Lustre mounts, including MGS, MDS, and obdfilter exports.

LNet BK
LNet BK refers to the LNet Backing Kernel, which is part of the LNet networking stack used in the Lustre file system.

Lustre Networking
Lustre Networking (LNet) is a custom network API that provides communication infrastructure for Lustre file system services between clients and servers.<SEP>Lustre Networking is the communication infrastructure that enables interaction between Lustre components over different network technologies.

test batch
Test batch refers to a collection of named tests used in validating the functionality and performance of the Lustre file system.

point-to-point test
Point-to-point test is a type of individual test within a test batch, used to evaluate specific aspects of the Lustre file system.

Lustre component
Lustre component refers to any of the individual parts of the Lustre file system architecture, such as MGS, MDS, MDT, OSS, and clients.

configuration
Configuration refers to the setup and parameters defined for the Lustre file system, including storage, networking, and component interactions.

system architecture
System architecture describes the overall design and structure of the Lustre file system, including its components and their relationships.

network technology
Network technology refers to the communication methods used in the Lustre file system, such as Ethernet and InfiniBand.

data consistency
Data consistency refers to the state where all components of the Lustre file system maintain uniform and accurate data across MDTs and OSTs.

file system consistency
File system consistency ensures that the Lustre file system maintains correct and reliable data structures and metadata.

system maintenance
System maintenance involves activities like checking and repairing inconsistencies in the Lustre file system using tools like LFSCK.

linkEA
linkEA (Link Extended Attribute) is an extended attribute stored in a file that contains information about its parent FID and file name, used to reconstruct the full path of a file.

Layout EA
Layout EA (Extended Attribute) stores information about how a file's data is laid out across OSTs, including which objects are used and their locations.

POSIX
POSIX (Portable Operating System Interface) is a set of standards for operating systems, ensuring compatibility and portability of applications across different platforms.

Lustre File System Operation Manual
Lustre File System Operation Manual is a document that provides detailed instructions and guidance on using and managing the Lustre file system.<SEP>Lustre File System Operation Manual is a document that provides detailed instructions and technical specifications for using and managing the Lustre file system.

Ba
Ba is a translator of the Lustre File System Operation Manual, contributing to the localization of technical documentation.

李硕
李硕is a translator of the Lustre File System Operation Manual, contributing to the localization of technical documentation.

Lustre Client
Lustre Client is a computing node running Lustre client software that enables interaction with the Lustre file system. It includes components like the metadata client (MDC), object storage clients (OSC), and others.

Lustre File System
Lustre File System is a distributed file system designed for high-performance computing environments, supporting large-scale data storage and access.<SEP>Lustre File System is a distributed file system that allows multiple clients to access and modify files concurrently. It uses components like MDT, OST, and OSC to manage metadata and data storage.

LMV
LMV is a Logical Metadata Volume that aggregates metadata clients (MDC) to provide transparent access to all MDTs, allowing clients to view multiple MDTs as a single coherent namespace.

LOV
LOV is a Logical Object Volume that aggregates object storage clients (OSC) to provide transparent access to all OSTs, allowing clients to see all OSTs as a single coherent namespace.

Client
Client is a user or application that accesses the Lustre file system to read or write data.

InfiniBand
InfiniBand is a high-speed network technology often used in Lustre clusters for low-latency, high-bandwidth communication.

Ethernet
Ethernet is a common network technology used in Lustre clusters for general-purpose communication.

Lustre Cluster
Lustre Cluster refers to a large-scale deployment of the Lustre file system, consisting of multiple components like MDS, OSS, and clients.

MGT
Management Group (MGT) is a component of the Lustre file system that manages configuration and administrative tasks.

Lustre File System Components
Lustre File System Components include MDS, OSS, Clients, and various networking technologies like InfiniBand and Ethernet.

Storage Arrays
Storage Arrays are enterprise-class storage solutions used in conjunction with the Lustre file system for large-scale data storage.

Commodity Storage
Commodity Storage refers to standard, cost-effective storage solutions that can be integrated with the Lustre file system.

SAN Fabric
SAN Fabric is a high-speed network infrastructure used for connecting storage devices in a Lustre environment.
